---
type: "FREE_CODING"
id: "3.2.1"
title: "Bank Account Validator"
description: "Create a BankAccount class with validation in the primary constructor using init blocks."
instructions: |
  Create a BankAccount class with:
  - accountNumber: String (read-only)
  - ownerName: String (read-only)  
  - balance: Double (mutable, starts with initialBalance)
  
  Validation rules in init block:
  1. accountNumber must not be blank
  2. accountNumber must be at least 8 characters
  3. ownerName must not be blank
  4. initialBalance must be >= 0
  
  Create an account with accountNumber="ACC123456", ownerName="John Doe", initialBalance=1000.0
  Then print: "Account ACC123456 owned by John Doe has balance $1000.0"
  
  If validation fails, throw an IllegalArgumentException with appropriate message.

language: "kotlin"
testCases:
  - id: "test-1"
    description: "Valid account creation"
    expectedOutput: "Account ACC123456 owned by John Doe has balance 1000.0"
    isVisible: true

hints:
  - level: 1
    text: "Use require() in the init block for validation"
  - level: 2
    text: "Check accountNumber.isNotBlank() and accountNumber.length >= 8"
  - level: 3
    text: "Format: class BankAccount(val accountNumber: String, val ownerName: String, initialBalance: Double)"

commonMistakes:
  - mistake: "Forgetting to make balance mutable"
    consequence: "Cannot deposit or withdraw later"
    correction: "Use var for balance, val for accountNumber and ownerName"
  - mistake: "Using wrong parameter name"
    consequence: "Confusion between parameter and property"
    correction: "The parameter initialBalance initializes the property balance"

difficulty: "intermediate"
---
